<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98434185694163></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98434185694163><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98434185694163>RE: Top five?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6400><span id=Scholar>ZomorSoulsaver</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>56 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 11th 3:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.32]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would Say the best Soloers are in this order from 1-5.<br>1. Necros-Can Solo from 1-50 without any trouble.<br>2. Druids-Can solo from 14-50 with no problems.<br>3. Magicians-Can solo from 4-30 and then given levels in between.<br>4. Monks-Can Solo once they get up to about level 12.<br>5. Paladins-Best melee class soloers because of root/blindness spell makes enemy run away/heals/new regen spell at 39/good buffs. EXCELLENT dungeon soloers, one of the only classes with the ability to solo in LowerGuk(trust me on this one).<br>Just my output.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
