<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98419677953457></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98419677953457><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98419677953457>RE: Top five?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 9th 10:59 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I must say that I have to disagree with some of the other here I would have to rate it this way.<br><br>1) Druids - If you look all the way from 1 to 60, Druids are the best soloers going. Their ability to solo yellow mobs into their 40's, and quad kite has to put them over the edge on this.<br><br>2) Necros - Possibly the best choice if you want to be able to solo and have very lil downtime. I know that I love my Necro for Soloin.<br><br>3) Wizards - Adequate soloers at lower levels, but in upper levels Wizards are able to start quad kiting and are simply amazing for Soloing.<br><br>4) Shadow Knights - Not great soloers in the mid levels (although still very possible), by later levels they are the best true melee soloer.<br><br>5) Bards - Much like Shadow Knights Bards may have some problems soloing for a few levels, but once they get their Fear Song, they may be one of the best Soloers out there in the later levels.<br><br>6) Mages - The mage pet is great, but unfortunately there you have to be very careful about the Mob that you try to solo. You will also have a great deal of down time unless you have <br>clarity. There also is no way to quad kite so you can not boost your efficiency. The one plus about the Mage is, it is possible to solo indoors. Mages also are one of the best classes for farming indoors (assuming lots of green mobs). A mage pet is very good at handling multiple green mobs with a lil AE help.<br><br>7) Enchanters. An enchanter with JBoots may be the best soloer out there. Although I've never played an enchanter, a good enchanter can Solo very efficiently with the Charm method. Allowing one mob to kill another, you get xp for the dead one and your charmed Mob may also be about dead, thus giving you two kills with very lil mana expence. Let me add, this method seems the most challenging, but also most exciting. I hope I can start an enchanter soon.<br><br>This is of course my opinion, but quad kiting and fear certainly makes for the best soloers all around.<br><br>I must also disagree with the statement that all classes can solo equally well, and that it all depends on the player. Certain classes are inherantly more adept at soloing. For example, although a cleric can solo, the spells that they have do not lend to soloing very efficiently.<br><br>Good Luck to you,<br><br>Peredur<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
